obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (1762)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short titles, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1762&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Veterinary`
  line `Council Act, 1984.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends, in the first instance, to the whole of the States of Haryana, Bihar, Orissa, Himachal`
  line `Pradesh and Rajasthan and to all Union territories^1 ; and it shall also extend to such other States as may`
  line `adopt this Act by resolution passed in that behalf in pursuance of clause (1) of article 252 of the`
  line Constitution.
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force in a State or Union territory to which it extends, or may become extended`
  line `in future, on such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint`
  line `and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act or for different States or Union`
  line territories.
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Extended to the Union territory of Jummu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (1763)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1763&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Council" means the Veterinary Council of India established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "member" means a member of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "President" means the President of the Council;`
  line
  line `(e) "recognised veterinary qualification" means any of the veterinary qualifications included in`
  line `the First Schedule or the Second Schedule;`
  line
  line `(f) "register" means a register maintained under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "registered veterinary practitioner" means a person whose name is for the time being duly`
  line `registered in a register;`
  line
  line `(h) "regulation" means a regulation made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "State Veterinary Council" means a Veterinary Council established under section 32 and`
  line `includes a Joint State Veterinary Council established in accordance with an agreement under`
  line `section 33;`
  line
  line `(j) "veterinary institution" means any University or other institution within or without India`
  line `which grants degrees, diplomas or licences in veterinary science and animal husbandry;`
  line
  line `(k) "veterinary medicine" means modern scientific veterinary medicine in all its branches and`
  line `includes veterinary surgery and obstetrics;`
  line
  line `(l) "Vice-President" means the Vice-President of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (1764)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and composition of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1764&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established`
  line `a Council to be called the Veterinary Council of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract and shall by the said name sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) five members to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst Directors of Animal`
  line `Husbandry (by whatever name called) of those States to which this Act extends;`
  line
  line `(b) four members to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst the heads of`
  line `veterinary institutions in the States to which this Act extends;`
  line
  line `(c) one member to be nominated by the Indian Council of Agricultural Research;`
  line
  line `(d) the Animal Husbandry Commissioner, Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one member to be nominated by the Central Government to represent the Ministry of the`
  line `Central Government dealing with animal husbandry;`
  line
  line `(f) one member to be nominated by the Indian Veterinary Association;`
  line
  line `(g) eleven members to be elected from amongst themselves by persons enrolled in the Indian`
  line `veterinary practitioners register;`
  line
  line `(h) one member to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst the Presidents of the`
  line `State Veterinary Councils of those States to which this Act extends;`
  line
  line `(i) one member to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst the Presidents of the`
  line `State Veterinary Associations of those States to which this Act extends;`
  line
  line `(j) Secretary, Veterinary Council of India, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(4) The President and Vice-President shall be elected by the members from amongst themselves in`
  line `such manner as may be provided by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) Whenever there is a vacancy in the office of the President, the Vice-President shall discharge the`
  line `functions of the President.`
  line
  line `(6) The names of persons nominated or elected as members shall be notified by the Central`
  line `Government in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(7) A person shall not be qualified for nomination or election to the Council unless he holds a`
  line `recognised veterinary qualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (1765)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Mode of election of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1765&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) An election under clause (g) of sub-section (3) of section 3`
  line `shall be conducted by the Central Government in accordance with such rules as may be made by it in this`
  line `behalf and any rule so made may provide that pending the preparation of the Indian veterinary`
  line `practitioners register in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the members referred to in that clause`
  line `may be nominated by the Central Government instead of being elected as provided therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any dispute arises regarding any election to the Council, it shall be referred to the Central`
  line `Government for its decision which shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (1766)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Term of office of President, Vice-President and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1766&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President or Vice-President`
  line `shall hold office for a term not exceeding three years and not extending beyond the expiry of his term as a`
  line member.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this section, a member, other than an ex officio member, shall hold`
  line `office for a term of three years from the date of his election or nomination to the Council or until his`
  line `successor shall have been duly elected or nominated, whichever is longer.`
  line
  line `(3) Members of the Council shall be eligible for re-nomination or re-election.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the term of three years is about to expire in respect of any member, a successor may be`
  line `nominated or elected at any time within three months before the said term expires, but, he shall not`
  line `assume office until the said term has expired.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (1767)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Cessation of membership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1767&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) A member shall be deemed to have vacated his office--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is absent without excuse, sufficient in the opinion of the Council, from three consecutive`
  line `meetings of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) if he ceases to hold the post from which he has been nominated;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a member elected under clause (g) of sub-section (3) of section 3, if he ceases to`
  line `be a person enrolled in the register;`
  line
  line `(d) if he has been convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude and punishable with`
  line imprisonment;
  line
  line `(e) if he is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(f) if he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court.`
  line
  line `(2) On the occurrence of a vacancy referred to in sub-section (1), the President shall forthwith report`
  line `the fact of such vacancy to the Central Government and thereafter that Government may, subject to the`
  line `proviso to section 7, take necessary steps to fill such vacancy.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1768)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1768&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `A casual vacancy in the Council shall be filled by nomination or election, as`
  line `the case may be, and the person nominated or elected to fill the vacancy shall hold office only for the`
  line `remainder of the term for which the member whose place he takes was nominated or elected:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such casual vacancy occurring within three months of the date of expiry of the`
  line `normal term of office of a nominated or an elected member need be filled under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1769)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Resignation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1769&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President or Vice-President may at any time resign his office by notice in`
  line `writing addressed to the Council and delivered to the Secretary and the resignation shall take effect from`
  line `the date on which it is accepted by the Council or on the expiry of ninety days from the date of receipt of`
  line `the resignation by the Secretary, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) A member may at any time resign his office by notice in writing addressed to the President and`
  line `every such resignation shall take effect from the date on which it is accepted by the President or on the`
  line `expiry of ninety days from the date of receipt of the resignation by the President, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1770)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Meetings of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1770&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall meet at least twice in a year at such time and`
  line `place as may be appointed by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The quorum necessary for the transaction of business at a meeting of the Council shall be nine.`
  line
  line `(3) The President when present shall preside at every meeting of the Council and in his absence the`
  line `Vice-President and in the absence of both any other member elected by the members present from`
  line `amongst themselves shall preside at such meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all questions which come up before any meeting of the`
  line `Council shall be decided by a majority of the members present and voting.`
  line
  line `(5) In the case of an equality of votes, the President shall have a casting vote.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (1) to (5), the Council shall observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to transaction of business at its meetings as may be provided by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1771)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Vacancies in the Council not to invalidate acts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1771&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Council shall`
  line `be invalid by reason only of the existence of a vacancy in the council or on account of any defect or`
  line `irregularity in its constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1772)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Appointment of Secretary and other officers or servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1772&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Central Government, appoint a Secretary (who shall also act as Treasurer unless`
  line `the Council appoints any other person as Treasurer) and may appoint such other officers and employees`
  line `as it may deem necessary to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the Secretary, other officers and employees appointed by`
  line `the Council shall be such as may be provided by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Secretary, officers and other employees of the Council shall be deemed to the public servants`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(4) All orders and decisions and other instruments of the Council shall be authenticated by the`
  line `signature of the Secretary or any other officer of the Council duly authorised by it in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1773)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Executive Committee and other Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1773&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall appoint from among its`
  line `members an Executive Committee and may constitute other Committees for such general or specific`
  line `purposes as the Council considers necessary and may co-opt any person or persons specially qualified to`
  line `advise on any matter to any Committee other than the Executive Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) A Committee constituted under this section shall meet at such time and at such places and shall`
  line `observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be provided`
  line `by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1774)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Fees and allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1774&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The President and other members and the members of the Committees`
  line `(other than the members of the Council) shall be paid such fees and allowances for attending the meetings`
  line `of the Council and the Committees as may be provided by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (1775)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Information to be furnished by the Council and publication thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1775&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall`
  line `furnish such reports, copies of its minutes, abstract of its accounts and other information to the Central`
  line `Government as that Government may require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may publish in such manner as it may think fit any report, copy, abstract`
  line `or other information furnished to it under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (1776)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Recognition of veterinary qualifications granted by veterinary institutions in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1776&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `veterinary qualifications granted by any veterinary institution in India which are included in the First`
  line `Schedule shall be recognised veterinary qualifications for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any veterinary institution in India which grants a veterinary qualification not included in the First`
  line `Schedule may apply to the Central Government to have such qualification recognised and the Central`
  line `Government, after consulting the Council, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the First`
  line `Schedule so as to include such qualification therein and any such notification may also direct that an entry`
  line `shall be made in the last column of the First Schedule against such veterinary qualification declaring that`
  line `it shall be a recognised veterinary qualification only when granted after a specified date.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (1777)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Recognition of veterinary qualifications granted by veterinary institutions in countries with which there is a scheme of reciprocity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1777&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The veterinary qualifications granted by veterinary`
  line `institutions outside India which are included in the Second Schedule shall be recognised veterinary`
  line `qualifications for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may enter into negotiations with the authority in any country outside India which by`
  line `the law of such country is entrusted with the maintenance of a register of veterinary practitioners, for the`
  line `setting of a scheme of reciprocity for the recognition of veterinary qualifications, and in pursuance of any`
  line `such scheme, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Second Schedule so as to include therein the veterinary qualification which the Council has decided should be`
  line `recognised, and any such notification may also direct that an entry shall be made in the last column of the`
  line `Second Schedule against such veterinary qualification declaring that it shall be a recognised veterinary`
  line `qualification only when granted after a specified date.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government, after consultation with the Council, may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, amend the Second Schedule by directing that an entry be made therein in respect of any`
  line `veterinary qualification declaring that it shall be a recognised veterinary qualification only when granted`
  line `before a specified date.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Council has refused to recommend any veterinary qualification which has been`
  line `proposed for recognition by any authority referred to in sub-section (2) and the authority applies to the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf, the Central Government, after considering such application and after`
  line `obtaining from the Council a report, if any, as to the reasons for any such refusal, may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, amend the Second Schedule so as to include such qualification therein and the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) shall apply to such notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (1778)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Special provisions in certain cases for recognition of veterinary qualifications granted by veterinary institutions in countries with which there is no scheme of reciprocity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1778&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government, after consultation with the Council, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that`
  line `the veterniary qualifications granted by veterinary institutions in any country outside India in respect of`
  line `which a scheme of reciprocity for the recognition of veterinary qualifications is not in force shall be`
  line `recognised veterinary qualification for the purposes of this Act or shall be so only when granted after a`
  line `specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that veterinary practice by persons possessing such qualifications--`
  line
  line `(a) shall be permitted only if such persons are enrolled as veterinary practitioners in accordance`
  line `with the law regulating the registration of veterinary practitioners for the time being in force in that`
  line country;
  line
  line `(b) shall be limited to the institution to which they are attached for the time being for the purpose`
  line `of teaching, research work, charitable work; and`
  line
  line `(c) shall be limited to the period specified in this behalf by the Central Government by general or`
  line `special order.`
  line
  line `(2) In respect of any such veterinary qualification, the Central Government, after consultation with`
  line `the Council, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that it shall be a recognised veterinary`
  line `qualification only when granted before a specified date.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (1779)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to require information as to courses of study and examinations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1779&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every veterinary`
  line `institution in a State which grants a recognised veterinary qualification shall furnish such information as`
  line `the Council may from time to time require as to the courses of study and examinations to be undergone in`
  line `order to obtain such qualification, as to the ages at which such courses of study and examinations are`
  line `required to be undergone and such qualification is conferred and generally as to the requisites for`
  line `obtaining such qualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (1780)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Inspection of veterinary institutions and examinations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1780&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Committee constituted under`
  line `section 12 may, subject to regulations, if any, made by the Council, appoint such number of veterinary`
  line `inspectors as it may deem requisite to inspect any veterinary institution or any college or other institution`
  line `where veterinary education is given or to attend any examination held by any veterinary institution for the`
  line `purpose of recommending to the Central Government recognition of veterinary qualification granted by`
  line `that veterinary institution.`
  line
  line `(2) The veterinary inspectors shall not interfere with the conduct of any training or examination, but`
  line `shall report to the Committee on the adequacy of the standards of veterinary education including staff,`
  line `equipment, accommodation, training and other facilities prescribed by regulations for giving veterinary`
  line `education or on the sufficiency of every examination which they attend.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall forward a copy of any such report to the veterinary institution concerned and`
  line `shall also forward a copy with remarks, if any, of the said institution thereon, to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (1781)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Appointment of visitors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1781&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may appoint such number of visitors as it may deem`
  line `requisite to inspect any veterinary institution or any college or other institution where veterinary`
  line `education is given or to attend any examination held by any veterinary institution for the purpose of`
  line `granting any recognised veterinary qualification.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person, whether he is a member or not, may be appointed as a visitor under this section, but a`
  line `person who is appointed as an inspector under section 19 for any inspection or examination shall not be`
  line `appointed as a visitor for the same inspection or examination.`
  line
  line `(3) The visitors shall not interfere with the conduct of any training or examination, but shall report to`
  line `the President on the adequacy of the standards of veterinary education including staff, equipment,`
  line `accommodation, training and other facilities prescribed by regulations for giving veterinary education or`
  line `on the sufficiency of every examination which they attend.`
  line
  line `(4) The report of a visitor shall be treated as confidential unless in any particular case the President`
  line `otherwise directs:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government requires a copy of the report of the visitor, the Council shall`
  line `furnish the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (1782)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Withdrawal of recognition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1782&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) When upon report by the Committee or the visitor, it appears`
  line `to the Council--`
  line
  line `(a) that the courses of study and examinations to be undergone in, or the proficiency required`
  line `from candidates at any examination held by, any veterinary institution, are not in conformity with the`
  line `regulations made under this Act or fall short of the standards required thereby, or`
  line
  line `(b) that the staff, equipment, accommodation, training and other facilities for instruction and`
  line `training provided in such veterinary institution or in any college or other institution affiliated to it do`
  line `not conform to the standards prescribed by the Council.`
  line
  line `the Council shall make a representation to that effect to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) After considering such representation, the Central Government may send it to the State`
  line `Government of the State in which the veterinary institution is situated and the State Government shall`
  line `forward it along with such remarks as it may choose to make to the veterinary institution, with an`
  line `intimation of the period within which that institution may submit its explanation to the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of the explanation or, where no explanation is submitted within the period fixed, then`
  line `on the expiry of that period, the State Government shall make its recommendation to the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government, after making such inquiry, if any, as it may deem fit, may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that an entry shall be made in the appropriate Schedule against`
  line `the said veterinary qualification declaring that it shall be a recognised veterinary qualification only when`
  line `granted before a specified date or that the said veterinary qualification if granted to students of a specified`
  line `college or institution affiliated to any veterinary institution shall be a recognised veterinary qualification`
  line `only when granted before a specified date or, as the case may be, that the said veterinary qualification`
  line `shall be a recognised veterinary qualification in relation to a specified college or institution affiliated to`
  line `any veterinary institution only when granted after a specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing such notification the Central Government may consult the Indian Council`
  line `of Agricultural Research.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (1783)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Minimum standards of veterinary education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1783&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, by regulations, specify`
  line `the minimum standards of veterinary education required for granting recognised veterinary qualifications`
  line `by veterinary institutions in those States to which this Act extends.`
  line
  line `(2) Copies of the draft regulations and of all subsequent amendments thereof shall be furnished by the`
  line `Council to the State Government concerned and the Council shall, before submitting such regulations or`
  line `any amendments thereof, as the case may be, to the Central Government for approval, take into consideration the comments of the State Government received within three months from the furnishing of`
  line `the copies as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, before approving such regulations or any amendments thereof,`
  line `consult the Indian Council of Agricultural Research.`
  line
  line `(4) The Committee constituted under section 12 shall from time to time report to the Council on the`
  line `efficacy of the regulations and may recommend to the Council such amendments thereof as it may think`
  line fit.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (1784)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Indian veterinary practitioners register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1784&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall, as soon as may be after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, cause to be maintained in such form and in such manner as may be provided`
  line `by regulations a register of veterinary practitioners to be known as the Indian veterinary practitioners`
  line `register which shall contain the names of all persons who possess the recognised veterinary qualifications`
  line `and who are for the time being enrolled on a State veterinary register of the State to which this Act`
  line extends.
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Secretary of the Council to keep the Indian veterinary practitioners`
  line `register in accordance with the provisions of this Act and of any orders made by the Council, and from`
  line `time to time to revise the register and publish it in the Gazette of India or in such other manner as may be`
  line `provided by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Such register shall be deemed to be a public document within the meaning of the Indian Evidence`
  line `Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), and may be proved by a copy published in the Gazette of India.`
  line
  line `(4) Each State Veterinary Council shall furnish to the Council six printed copies of the State`
  line `veterinary register as soon as may be after the 1st day of April of each year and each State Veterinary`
  line `Council shall inform the Council without delay of all additions to, and other amendments in, the State`
  line `veterinary register made from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (1785)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Registration in the Indian veterinary practitioners register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1785&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Secretary of the Council`
  line `may, on receipt of the report of registration of a person in a State veterinary register or on an application`
  line `made in such form and in such manner, as may be provided by regulations, by any such person, enter his`
  line `name in the Indian veterinary practitioners register:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Secretary is satisfied that the person concerned possesses a recognised veterinary`
  line qualification.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (1786)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Issue of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1786&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person whose name has been entered in the Indian`
  line `veterinary practitioners register shall, on an application made in this behalf in such form and in such`
  line `manner and on payment of such fees, not exceeding fifteen rupees, as may be provided by regulations, be`
  line `entitled to a certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Council shall grant to the applicant a`
  line `certificate of registration in such form as may be provided by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that on the removal of his name from a register, such certificate shall cease to be valid.`
  line
  line `(3) Where it is shown to the satisfaction of the Secretary of the Council that a certificate of`
  line `registration has been lost or destroyed, the Secretary may, on payment of such fees, not exceeding ten`
  line `rupees, as may be specified by regulations, issue a duplicate certificate in such form as may be specified`
  line `in the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (1787)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Registration of additional qualifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1787&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person whose name is entered in the`
  line `Indian veterinary practitioners register obtains any post-graduate degree or diploma in veterinary science`
  line `in addition to his recognised veterinary qualification, he shall, on an application made in this behalf in`
  line `such form and in such manner and on payment of such fees, not exceeding fifteen rupees, as may be`
  line `provided by regulations, be entitled to have an entry stating such degree or diploma made against his`
  line `name in such register in addition to any entry previously made.`
  line
  line `(2) The entries in respect of any such person in a State veterinary register shall be altered in`
  line `accordance with the alterations made in the Indian veterinary practitioners register.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (1788)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Removal of names from the Indian veterinary practitioners register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1788&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If the name of any`
  line `person enrolled on a State veterinary register is removed therefrom in pursuance of any power conferred`
  line `under this Act, the Council shall direct the removal of the name of such person from the Indian veterinary`
  line `practitioners register.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (1789)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Person enrolled on Indian veterinary practitioners register to notify change of place of residence or practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1789&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Every person registered in the Indian veterinary practitioners register shall notify`
  line `any transfer of the place of his residence or practice to the Council and the State Veterinary Council`
  line `within ninety days of such transfer, failing which his right to participate in the election of members of the`
  line `Council or a State Veterinary Council shall be liable to be forfeited by order of the Central Government`
  line `either permanently or for such period as may be specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (1790)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Privileges of persons, who are enrolled on the Indian veterinary practitioners register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1790&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the conditions and restrictions laid down in this Act, every person whose name is for the time`
  line `being borne on the Indian veterinary practitioners register shall be entitled according to his qualifications`
  line `to practise as a veterinary practitioner and to recover in due course of law in respect of such practice any`
  line `expenses, charges in respect of medicaments and other appliances or any fees to which he may be`
  line entitled.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (1791)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Right of persons who are enrolled on the Indian veterinary practitioners register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1791&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line No
  line `person, other than a registered veterinary practitioner, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office as veterinary physician or surgeon or any other like office (by whatever name`
  line `called) in Government or in any institution maintained by a local or other authority;`
  line
  line `(b) practise veterinary medicine in any State:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, by order, permit a person holding a diploma or`
  line `certificate of veterinary supervisor, stockman or stock assistant (by whatever name called) issued by`
  line `the Directorate of Animal Husbandry (by whatever name called) of any State or any veterinary`
  line `institution in India, to render, under the supervision and direction of a registered veterinary`
  line `practitioner, minor veterinary services.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--"Minor veterinary services" means the rendering of preliminary veterinary aid,`
  line `like, vaccination, castration, and dressing of wounds, and such other types of preliminary aid or the`
  line `treatment of such ailments as the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) be entitled to sign or authenticate a veterinary health certificate or any other certificate`
  line `required by any law to be signed or authenticated by a duly qualified veterinary practitioner;`
  line
  line `(d) be entitled to give evidence at any inquest or in any court of law as an expert under section 45`
  line `of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), on any matter relating to veterinary medicine.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (1792)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Professional conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1792&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, by regulations, specify standards of professional`
  line `conduct and etiquette and a code of ethics for veterinary practitioners.`
  line
  line `(2) Regulations made by the Council under sub-section (1) may specify which violations thereof shall`
  line `constitute infamous conduct in any professional respect, that is to say, professional misconduct, and such`
  line `provisions shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line force.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (1793)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Establishment and composition of State Veterinary Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1793&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except where a Joint State`
  line `Veterinary Council is established in accordance with an agreement made under section 33, the State`
  line `Government shall establish a State Veterinary Council consisting of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) four members elected from among themselves by veterinary practitioners registered in the`
  line `State veterinary register;`
  line
  line `(b) the heads of veterinary institutions, if any, in the State, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) three members nominated by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(d) the Director of Veterinary Services of the State (by whatever name called), ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one member to be nominated by the State Veterinary Association, if any;`
  line
  line `(f) Registrar of the State Veterinary Council, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(2) The names of persons nominated or elected as members shall be notified by the State Government`
  line `in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for nomination or election as a member of the State Veterinary`
  line `Council unless he holds a recognised veterinary qualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (1794)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Inter-State agreements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1794&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Two or more State Governments may enter into an agreement to`
  line `be in force for such period and to be subject to renewal for further periods, if any, as may be specified in`
  line `the agreement to provide--`
  line
  line `(a) for the establishment of a Joint State Veterinary Council for all participating States; or`
  line
  line `(b) for the State Veterinary Council of one State to serve the needs of the other participating`
  line States.
  line
  line `(2) In addition to such matters as are in this Act specified, an agreement under this section may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide for the apportionment between the participating States of the expenditure in`
  line `connection with the State Veterinary Council or Joint State Veterinary Council;`
  line
  line `(b) determine which of the participating State Governments shall exercise the several functions of`
  line `the State Government under this Act and the references in this Act to the State Government shall be`
  line `construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(c) provide for consultation between the participating State Governments either generally or with`
  line `reference to particular matters arising under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) make such incidental and ancillary provisions not inconsistent with this Act as may be`
  line `deemed necessary or expedient for giving effect to the agreement.`
  line
  line `(3) An agreement under this section shall be published in the Official Gazettes of the participating`
  line States.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (1795)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Composition of Joint State Veterinary Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1795&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Joint State Veterinary Council shall`
  line `consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) two members elected from among themselves by veterinary practitioners registered in the`
  line `register of each of the participating States;`
  line
  line `(b) the heads of veterinary institutions, if any, in the participating States, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) two members nominated by each participating State Government;`
  line
  line `(d) the Director of Veterinary Services of each of the participating States, by whatever name`
  line `called, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one nominee of the State Veterinary Associations, if any, of each of the participating States;`
  line
  line `(f) Registrar of the Joint State Veterinary Council, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(2) The names of the persons nominated or elected as members shall be notified by the State`
  line `Governments in the Official Gazettes of the States.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for nomination or election as a member of the Joint State`
  line `Veterinary Council unless he holds a recognised veterinary qualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (1796)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Incorporation of State Veterinary Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1796&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Every State Veterinary Council shall be a body`
  line `corporate by such name as may be notified by the State Government in the Official Gazette or, in the case`
  line `of a Joint State Veterinary Council, as may be determined in the agreement, having perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal with power to acquire and hold property, both movable and immovable, and shall by`
  line `the said name sue or be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (1797)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title President.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1797&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The President of the State Veterinary Council shall be elected by the members of`
  line `that Council from amongst themselves in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (1798)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Mode of elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1798&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The election under this Chapter shall be conducted in the prescribed manner`
  line `and where any dispute arises regarding any such election, it shall be referred to the State Government for`
  line `its decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (1799)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Terms of office and causal vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1799&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, a member`
  line `of the State Veterinary Council, other than an ex officio member, shall hold office for a term of three`
  line `years from the date of his election or nomination to the State Veterinary Council or until his successor has`
  line `been duly elected or nominated, whichever is longer:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member of the State Veterinary Council nominated under clause (c) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 32 or clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 34, shall hold office during the pleasure of the`
  line `authority nominating him.`
  line
  line `(2) Members of the State Veterinary Council shall be eligible for re-election or re-nomination, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) An elected or nominated member of the State Veterinary Council shall be deemed to have vacated`
  line `his office--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is absent without excuse, sufficient in the opinion of the State Veterinary Council, from`
  line `three consecutive meetings of the State Veterinary Council;`
  line
  line `(b) if he ceases to hold the office from which he has been nominated;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a member whose name is required to be included in any State veterinary`
  line `register, if his name is removed from the register;`
  line
  line `(d) if he has been convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude and punishable with`
  line imprisonment;
  line
  line `(e) if he is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(f) if he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court.`
  line
  line `(4) No act done by the State Veterinary Council shall be called in question on the ground merely of`
  line `the existence of any vacancy, or defect, in the establishment of, the State Veterinary Council.`
  line
  line `(5) A casual vacancy in the State Veterinary Council shall be filled by fresh election or nomination,`
  line `as the case may be, and the person elected or nominated to fill the vacancy shall hold office only for the`
  line `remainder of the term for which the member whose place he takes was elected or nominated.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Veterinary Council shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to transaction of`
  line `business at its meetings as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (1800)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title Resignation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1800&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of the State Veterinary Council may at any time resign his office`
  line `by notice in writing addressed to the State Veterinary Council and delivered to the Registrar and the resignation shall take effect from the date on which it is accepted by that Council or on the expiry of`
  line `ninety days from the date of receipt of the resignation by the Registrar, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) A member of the State Veterinary Council may at any time resign his office by notice in writing`
  line `addressed to the President of the State Veterinary Council and every such resignation shall take effect`
  line `from the date on which it is accepted by the President or on the expiry of ninety days from the date of`
  line `receipt of the resignation by the President, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (1801)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Executive and other Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1801&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be`
  line `prescribed, the State Veterinary Council may constitute an Executive Committee and other Committees`
  line `for exercising any power or discharging any duty of the State Veterinary Council or for inquiring into,`
  line `reporting with respect to, or advising on, any matter which the State Veterinary Council may refer to`
  line them.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (1802)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Fees and allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1802&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The President and other members of the State Veterinary Council and the`
  line `members of the Committees (other than the members of the State Veterinary Council) shall be paid such`
  line `fees and allowances for attending the meetings of the State Veterinary Council and the Committees as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (1803)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Appointment of Registrar and other officers or servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1803&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Veterinary Council`
  line `may, with the previous sanction of the State Government, appoint a Registrar who shall also act as`
  line `Treasurer unless the State Veterinary Council appoints any person as Treasurer and may appoint such`
  line `other officers and employees as it may deem necessary to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the Registrar, and of the other officers and employees`
  line `appointed by the State Veterinary Council shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar and other officers and employees of the State Veterinary Council shall be deemed to`
  line `be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(4) All orders and decisions and other instruments of the State Veterinary Council shall be`
  line `authenticated by the signature of the Registrar or any other officer of the State Veterinary Council duly`
  line `authorised by it in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), for the first two years from the first`
  line `constitution of the State Veterinary Council the Registrar of the State Veterinary Council shall be a person`
  line `appointed by the State Government, who shall hold office during the pleasure of the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (1804)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Information to be furnished by State Veterinary Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1804&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Veterinary Council`
  line `shall furnish such reports, copies of its minutes and of the minutes of the Executive Committee and`
  line `abstract of its accounts to the State Government as the State Government may from time to time require`
  line `and shall forward to the Council copies of all material so furnished to the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may publish in such manner as it thinks fit any report, copy or abstract`
  line `furnished to it under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (1805)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Preparation and maintenance of State veterinary practitioners register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1805&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government shall as soon as may be cause to be prepared in the manner hereinafter provided a register of`
  line `veterinary practitioners to be known as the State veterinary register for the State.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Veterinary Council shall on its establishment assume the duty of maintaining the State`
  line `veterinary register in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The State veterinary register shall contain the names of the persons possessing the recognised`
  line `veterinary qualifications.`
  line
  line `(4) The State veterinary register shall include the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the full name, nationality and residential address of the registered person;`
  line
  line `(b) the date of his admission in the State veterinary register;`
  line
  line `(c) his qualification for registration and the date on which he obtained such qualification and`
  line `authority which conferred it;`
  line
  line `(d) his professional address; and`
  line
  line `(e) such further particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (1806)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `First preparation of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1806&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of first preparing the State veterinary`
  line `register, the State Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a Registration`
  line `Tribunal consisting of three persons holding recognised veterinary qualifications and shall also appoint a`
  line `Registrar who shall act as Secretary of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, by the same or a like notification, appoint a date on or before which`
  line `application for registration, which shall be accompanied by the prescribed fee, not exceeding twenty-five`
  line `rupees, shall be made to the Registration Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registration Tribunal shall examine every application received on or before the appointed`
  line `date, and, if it is satisfied that the applicant is qualified for registration under section 46, shall direct the`
  line `entry of the name of the applicant on the register.`
  line
  line `(4) The register so prepared shall thereafter be published in such manner as the State Government`
  line `may direct, and any person aggrieved by a decision of the Registration Tribunal expressed or implied in`
  line `the register as so published may, within sixty days from the date of such publication, appeal to an`
  line `authority appointed by the State Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) The Registrar shall amend the register in accordance with the decisions of the authority appointed`
  line `under sub-section (4) and shall thereupon issue to every person whose name is entered in the register a`
  line `certificate of registration in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(6) Upon the establishment of the State Veterinary Council, the register shall be given into its`
  line `custody, and the State Government may direct that all or any specified part of the application fees for`
  line `registration in the first register shall be paid to the credit of the State Veterinary Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (1807)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Qualifications for entry on preparation of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1807&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be entitled, on payment of`
  line `the prescribed fee not exceeding twenty-five rupees, to have his name entered on the State veterinary`
  line `register if he resides in the State and if he holds a recognised veterinary qualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (1808)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Scrutiny of applications for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1808&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the date appointed for the receipt of`
  line `applications for registration under sub-section (2) of section 45, all applications for registration shall be`
  line `addressed to the Registrar of the State Veterinary Council and shall be accompanied by the prescribed fee`
  line `not exceeding twenty-five rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If upon such application the Registrar of the State Veterinary Council is of the opinion that the`
  line `applicant is entitled to have his name entered on the State veterinary register, he shall enter thereon the`
  line `name of the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person, whose name has under the provisions of this Act been removed from the`
  line `State veterinary register of any State, shall be entitled to have his name entered on the State veterinary`
  line `register of another State except with the approval of the State Veterinary Council from whose register his`
  line `name was removed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person whose application for registration is rejected by the Registrar of the State Veterinary`
  line `Council may, within three months from the date of such rejection, appeal to the State Veterinary Council.`
  line
  line `(4) A person aggrieved by the decision of the State Veterinary Council under sub-section (3) may,`
  line `within sixty days from the communication to him of such decision, appeal to the State Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Upon entry in the State veterinary register of a name under this section, the Registrar of the State`
  line `Veterinary Council shall issue a certificate of registration in the prescribed form.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (1809)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Renewal fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1809&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that`
  line `for the retention of a name in the State veterinary register, there shall be paid in every five years to the State Veterinary Council, such renewal fee, not exceeding fifteen rupees, as may be prescribed and where`
  line `such direction has been made, such renewal fee shall be due to be paid before the 1st day of April of the`
  line `year to which it relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a renewal fee is not paid within the said period, the Registrar of the State Veterinary`
  line `Council shall remove the name of the defaulter from the State veterinary register:`
  line
  line `Provided that a name so removed may be restored to the said register on payment of renewal fee in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On payment of the renewal fee, the Registrar of the State Veterinary Council shall issue a`
  line `certificate of renewal and such certificate shall be proof of renewal of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (1810)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Removal from the register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1810&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, the State Veterinary`
  line `Council may order that the name of any person shall be removed from the State veterinary register where`
  line `it is satisfied after giving that person a reasonable opportunity of being heard and after such further`
  line `inquiry, if any, as it may think fit to make--`
  line
  line `(a) that his name has been entered in the State veterinary register by error or on account of`
  line `mis-representation or suppression of a material fact, or`
  line
  line `(b) that he has been convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude and punishable with`
  line `imprisonment or has been guilty of any infamous conduct in any professional respect or has violated`
  line `the standards of professional conduct and etiquette or the code of ethics which in the opinion of the`
  line `State Veterinary Council renders him unfit to be kept in the said register.`
  line
  line `(2) An order under sub-section (1) may direct that any person whose name is ordered to be removed`
  line `from the State veterinary register shall be ineligible for registration under this Act, either permanently or`
  line `for such period of years as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) An order under sub-section (1) shall not take effect until the expiry of three months from the date`
  line `thereof or until an appeal, if any on such order is finally disposed of, whichever date is later.`
  line
  line `(4) A person aggrieved by an order under sub-section (1) may, within sixty days from the`
  line `communication to him of such order, appeal to the Council.`
  line
  line `(5) A person aggrieved by the decision of the Council under sub-section (4) may, within sixty days`
  line `from the communication to him of such decision, appeal to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) A person whose name has been removed from the register under this section or under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 48 shall forthwith surrender his certificate of registration and certificate of`
  line `renewal, if any, to the Registrar of the State Veterinary Council and the name so removed shall be`
  line `published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(7) A person whose name has been removed from the State veterinary register under this section or`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 48 shall not be entitled to have his name registered in the State veterinary`
  line `register or in any other State veterinary register, except with the approval of the State Veterinary Council`
  line `from whose register his name has been removed.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (1811)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Restoration to State veterinary register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1811&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The State Veterinary Council may, at any time for`
  line `reasons appearing to it sufficient and subject to approval of the Council, order that upon payment of the`
  line `prescribed fee not exceeding twenty-five rupees, the name of a person removed from a State veterinary`
  line `register shall be restored thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (1812)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Printing of State veterinary register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1812&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the 1st day of April each year,`
  line `the Registrar of the State Veterinary Council shall cause to be printed copies of the State veterinary`
  line `register as it stood on the said date and such copies shall be made available to persons applying therefor`
  line `on payment of the prescribed charge not exceeding ten rupees and shall be evidence that on the said date`
  line `the persons whose names are entered therein were registered veterinary practitioners.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (1813)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Transfer of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1813&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Where a registered veterinary practitioner of one State is practising`
  line `veterinary medicine in another State, he may, on payment of prescribed fee which shall not exceed the`
  line `renewal fee for registration in such other State, make an application in the prescribed form to the Council`
  line `for the transfer of his name from the State veterinary register of the State where he is registered to the`
  line `State veterinary register of the State in which he is practising veterinary medicine, and on receipt of any`
  line `such application, the Council shall, notwithstanding anything contained elsewhere in this Act, direct that`
  line `the name of such person be removed from the first-mentioned State veterinary register and entered in the`
  line `State veterinary register of the second-mentioned State and the State Veterinary Councils concerned shall`
  line `comply with such direction:`
  line
  line `Provided that such a person shall be required to produce a certificate to the effect that all dues in`
  line `respect of his registration in the former State have been paid:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where any such application for transfer is made by a veterinary practitioner`
  line `against whom any disciplinary proceeding is pending or where for any other reason it appears to the`
  line `Council that the application for transfer has not been made bona fide and the transfer should not be made,`
  line `the Council may, after giving the veterinary practitioner a reasonable opportunity of making a`
  line `representation in this behalf, reject the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (1814)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1814&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `No order refusing to enter a name in a register or removing a name from a`
  line `register shall be called in question in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (1815)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Issue of duplicate certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1815&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Where it is shown to the satisfaction of the Registrar of the`
  line `State Veterinary Council that a certificate of registration or a certificate of renewal has been lost or`
  line `destroyed, the Registrar may, on payment of the prescribed fee, not exceeding ten rupees, issue a`
  line `duplicate certificate in the prescribed form.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (1816)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Penalty for falsely claiming to be registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1816&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `If any person whose name is not for the time`
  line `being entered in a register falsely represents that it is so entered or uses in connection with his name or`
  line `title any words or letters reasonably calculated to suggest that his name is so entered, he shall be`
  line `punishable on first conviction with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, and on any subsequent`
  line `conviction with imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine not exceeding one thousand`
  line `rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (1817)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Misuse of titles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1817&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `If any person,--`
  line
  line `(a) not being a person registered in a register, takes or uses the description of a veterinary`
  line `practitioner, or`
  line
  line `(b) not possessing a recognised veterinary qualification, uses a degree or a diploma or a licence or`
  line `an abbreviation indicating or implying such qualification,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable on first conviction with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, and on any`
  line `subsequent conviction with imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine not exceeding five`
  line `thousand rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (1818)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Practice by unregistered persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1818&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the expiry of one year from the date appointed`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 45, no person, other than a registered veterinary practitioner or a person`
  line `permitted by the State Government under the proviso to clause (b) of section 30 shall practise veterinary`
  line `medicine or render minor veterinary services, as the case may be, in that State.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), he shall be punishable on first`
  line `conviction with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, and on any subsequent conviction with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine not exceeding five thousand rupees or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (1819)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Failure to surrender certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1819&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `If any person whose name has been removed`
  line `from a register fails without sufficient cause forthwith to surrender his certificate of registration or certificate of renewal, or both, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees`
  line `and in case of a continuing offence with an additional fine which may extend to ten rupees per day after`
  line `the first day during which the offence continues..`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (1820)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Cognizance of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1820&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this`
  line `Act except upon complaint made by order of the State Government or State Veterinary Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (1821)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Bar of suit and other legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1821&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against the`
  line `Central Government or the State Government or the Council or a State Veterinary Council in respect of`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act, or of any rules,`
  line `regulations or orders made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (1822)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Payment of part of fees to Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1822&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `The State Veterinary Council shall, before the end of June`
  line `in each year, pay to the Council a sum equivalent to one-fourth of the total fees realised by the State`
  line `Veterinary Council under this Act during the period of twelve months ending on the 31st day of March of`
  line `that year.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (1823)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1823&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall maintain appropriate accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the balance sheet, in accordance with such`
  line `general directions as may be issued and in such form as may be specified by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Council shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India or any person appointed by him in this behalf and any expenditure incurred by him or any person so`
  line `appointed in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Council to the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Council shall have the same rights and privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books`
  line `of accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the office of the Council.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Council as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be forwarded annually`
  line `to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each House of`
  line Parliament.
  line
  line `(5) A copy of the accounts of the Council as so certified together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded simultaneously to the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (1824)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Appointment of Commission of Inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1824&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it appears to the Central Government`
  line `that the Council is not complying with any of the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may`
  line `appoint a Commission of Inquiry consisting of three persons, two of whom shall be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government, one being the Judge of a High Court and one by the Council and refer to it the`
  line `matter on which the inquiry is to be made.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall proceed to inquire in a summary manner and report to the Central`
  line `Government on the matters referred to it together with such remedies, if any, as the Commission may like`
  line `to recommend.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may accept the report or remit the same to the Commission for`
  line `modification or reconsideration.`
  line
  line `(4) After the report is finally accepted, the Central Government may order the Council to adopt the`
  line `remedies so recommended within such time as may be specified in the order and if the Council fails to`
  line `comply within the time so specified, the Central Government may pass such order or take such action as`
  line `may be necessary to give effect to the recommendations of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(5) Whenever it appears to the State Government that the State Veterinary Council is not complying`
  line `with any of the provisions of this Act, the State Government may likewise appoint a similar Commission of inquiry in respect of the State Veterinary Council to make inquiry in like manner and pass such orders`
  line `or take such action as specified in sub-sections (3) and (4).`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (1825)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1825&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of Chapters II, III, IV and V.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be, after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall,`
  line `thereafter, have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (1826)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1826&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of Chapters VI, VII and VIII.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the President of the State Veterinary Council shall be elected under`
  line `section 36;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which election under Chapter VI shall be conducted;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be observed by the State Veterinary Council at its meetings under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions and restrictions with respect to the constitution of Executive Committee and`
  line `other Committees under section 40;`
  line
  line `(e) the fees and allowances for attending the meetings of the State Veterinary Council and the`
  line `Committees under section 41;`
  line
  line `(f) the terms and conditions of appointment of the Registrar, other officers and employees of the`
  line `State Veterinary Council under sub-section (2) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(g) the particulars to be included in the State veterinary register under clause (e) of sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 44;`
  line
  line `(h) the fee which shall be accompanied by an application for registration under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 45 and sub-section (1) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of certificate of registration under sub-section (5) of section 45 and sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 47;`
  line
  line `(j) the fee payable under section 46, section 50, section 52 and section 54;`
  line
  line `(k) the renewal fee under sub-section (1) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of payment of renewal fee under the proviso to sub-section (2) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(m) the charge for supplying printed copies of the State veterinary register under section 51;`
  line
  line `(n) the form of duplicate certificate under section 54;`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed under Chapters VI, VII and VIII.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or, where such Legislature consists of one`
  line `House, before that House`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (1827)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1827&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, make regulations, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act and the rules made under`
  line `section 64, to carry out the purposes of Chapters II, III, IV and V.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the President and Vice-President shall be elected under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be observed respectively by the Council and the Committee at their meeting`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 9 and sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions of appointment of the Secretary, other officers and employees of the`
  line `Council under sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(d) the fees and allowances for attending the meetings of the Council and the Committees under`
  line `section 13;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner in which the Indian veterinary practitioners register shall be maintained`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of keeping the Indian veterinary practitioners register under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 23;`
  line
  line `(g) the form and manner in which an application may be made under section 24;`
  line
  line `(h) the form of application and the fee payable under sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of certificate of registration under sub-section (2) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(j) the fee payable under sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(k) the form of duplicate certificate under sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(l) the form and manner in which an application may be made and the fee payable under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(m) the standards of professional conduct and etiquette and code of ethics to be observed by`
  line `veterinary practitioners under sub-section (1) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter for which under this Act provision may be made by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation shall, as soon as may be after it is made by the Council, be forwarded to the`
  line `Central Government and that Government shall cause a copy of the same to be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the`
  line `regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall, thereafter,`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (1828)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559&sectionId=1828&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00005_198452_1517807325559
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `As from the commencement of this Act in any State, every other Act`
  line `relating to any matter contained in this Act and in force in that State shall, to the extent to which that Act`
  line `or any provision contained therein corresponds, or is repugnant, to this Act or any provision contained in`
  line `this Act, stand repealed and the provisions of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897),`
  line `shall apply to such repeal as if such other Act were a Central Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
